The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the Eighth Meeting of the National Space Council at the Kennedy Space Center in Cape Canaveral, Florida. He expressed gratitude to the members of the National Space Council and the User Advisory Group for their contributions to American leadership in space. Pence highlighted the progress made in the last four years, including the revival of the National Space Council, the focus on human space exploration, and the goal of returning to the Moon and eventually reaching Mars. He also emphasized the importance of American dominance in space and the challenges posed by other nations, particularly China and Russia. Pence announced the names of the Artemis astronauts who will lead the next missions to the Moon, including the first woman to set foot on the lunar surface. He concluded by expressing confidence in the future of American leadership in space and thanking all those who have contributed to the cause.